        <section id="sec-3-4" class="section">
          <h2 class="section-title">3.4 Agile Project Management</h2>
          <p class="paragraph">
            Scrum is an agile method focusing on managing iterative development...
          </p>

          <figure class="figure">
            <img src="sds/3.5.PNG" alt="Scrum Process" class="figure-img" />
            <figcaption class="figure-caption">
              <strong>Figure 3.5:</strong> The Scrum sprint process
            </figcaption>
          </figure>

          <div class="content-card">
            <h3 class="subsection-title">Scrum Process</h3>
            <ol class="list-ordered">
              <li><span class="highlight">Initial Phase:</span> Establish objectives...</li>
              <li><span class="highlight">Sprint Cycles:</span> 2-4 week iterations...</li>
              <li><span class="highlight">Project Closure:</span> Complete documentation...</li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <h3 class="subsection-title">Key Scrum Elements</h3>
          <div class="two-col-grid">
            <div class="content-card">
              <h4 class="info-title">Product Backlog</h4>
              <p class="info-text">Prioritized list of features managed by Product Owner</p>
            </div>
            <div class="content-card">
              <h4 class="info-title">Sprint Planning</h4>
              <p class="info-text">Team selects backlog items for sprint...</p>
            </div>
            <div class="content-card">
              <h4 class="info-title">Daily Scrum</h4>
              <p class="info-text">15-minute daily meeting to review progress...</p>
            </div>
            <div class="content-card">
              <h4 class="info-title">Sprint Review</h4>
              <p class="info-text">Demonstrate completed work to stakeholders</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 3.5 -->
        <section id="sec-3-5" class="section">
          <h2 class="section-title">3.5 Scaling Agile Methods</h2>
          <p class="paragraph">
            While agile methods work well for small teams...
          </p>

          <h3 class="subsection-title">Challenges in Scaling</h3>
          <div class="content-card">
            <ul class="list">
              <li><span class="highlight">System Complexity:</span> Large systems...</li>
              <li><span class="highlight">Legacy Integration:</span> Interaction with existing systems...</li>
              <li><span class="highlight">Configuration Management:</span> Significant effort in configuration...</li>
              <li><span class="highlight">External Constraints:</span> Regulations may require documentation...</li>
              <li><span class="highlight">Long Development Times:</span> Difficult to maintain teams...</li>
              <li><span class="highlight">Diverse Stakeholders:</span> Impossible to involve all stakeholders...</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="subsection-title">Scaling Up Strategies</h3>
          <p class="paragraph">
            To scale agile to large systems while maintaining core principles:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-ordered ml-4">
            <li>Invest in upfront architecture design and critical documentation</li>
            <li>Establish cross-team communication mechanisms</li>
            <li>Maintain frequent builds and regular releases</li>
            <li>Adapt configuration management tools for multi-team development</li>
          </ol>

          <h3 class="subsection-title">Scaling Out Across Organizations</h3>
          <p class="paragraph">
            Introducing agile methods organization-wide faces cultural...
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-4">
            <li>Management commitment and evangelists to promote change</li>
            <li>Adaptation of organizational standards...</li>
            <li>Significant resources devoted to cultural transformation</li>
            <li>Patience — organizational change takes time</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="paragraph">
            While few large organizations have fully transitioned to agile...
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
